16 p. 3793), as amended, particularly by an Act approved February 19, 2024 (Ga. L. 2024, p.
17 3560), is amended by revising subsection (b) of Section 1 as follows:
18 "(b)(1) Each resident of the City of Woodstock who is a senior citizen is granted an
19 exemption on that person's homestead from all City of Woodstock ad valorem taxes for
20 municipal purposes in the amount of the full value of that homestead, provided that such
21 resident or his or her spouse was lawfully granted a homestead exemption on his or her
22 current or former homestead within the city limits for at least five years before his or her
23 application for the exemption allowed under this subsection. Such five years are not
24 required to run consecutively or immediately precede such resident's application.
25 (2) Each resident of the City of Woodstock who was lawfully granted a homestead
26 exemption on his or her homestead under this section as it existed prior to the first day
27 of January of the year immediately prior to the effective date of this subsection and who
28 is a senior citizen shall be granted the homestead exemption allowed under paragraph (1)
29 of this subsection on his or her homestead within the city limits, without regard to the
30 five-year requirement, for each year that he or she is a senior citizen.
31 (3) Each resident of the City of Woodstock who is the surviving spouse of an individual
32 who was granted the exemption under paragraph (1) or (2) of this subsection shall be
33 granted the exemption allowed under paragraph (1) of this subsection on his or her
34 homestead within the city limits, without regard to the five-year requirement, for each
35 year that such surviving spouse is a senior citizen."
36 SECTION 2.
37 In accordance with the requirements of Article VII, Section II of the Constitution of the State
38 of Georgia, this Act shall not become law unless it receives the requisite two-thirds' majority
39 vote in both the Senate and the House of Representatives.
