40 SECTION 3.
41 The municipal election superintendent of the City of Woodstock shall call and conduct an
42 election as provided in this section for the purpose of submitting this Act to the electors of
43 the City of Woodstock for approval or rejection. The municipal election superintendent shall
44 conduct that election on any permissible special election date under Code Section 21-2-540
45 of the O.C.G.A., but not later than the November, 2026, general election and shall issue the
46 call and conduct such election as provided by general law. The municipal election
47 superintendent shall cause the date and purpose of the election to be published once a week
48 for two weeks immediately preceding the date thereof in the official organ of Cherokee
49 County. The ballot shall have written or printed thereon the words:
50 "( ) YES Shall the Act be approved which clarifies the five-year residency
51 ( ) NO requirement for a homestead exemption from City of Woodstock ad
52 valorem taxes for municipal purposes for residents who are 62 years of age
53 or older and waives such residency requirement for any such resident's
54 surviving spouse?"
55 All persons desiring to vote for approval of the Act shall vote "Yes," and all persons desiring
56 to vote for rejection of the Act shall vote "No." If more than one-half of the votes cast on
57 such question are for approval of the Act, Section 1 of this Act shall become of full force and
58 effect on the first day of January following the date of such election. If the Act is not so
59 approved or if the election is not conducted as provided in this section, Section 1 of this Act
60 shall not become effective, and this Act shall be automatically repealed on July 1, 2027. The
61 expense of such election shall be borne by the City of Woodstock. It shall be the municipal
62 election superintendent's duty to certify the result thereof to the Secretary of State. The
63 provisions of this section shall be mandatory upon the municipal election superintendent and
64 are not intended as directory. If the municipal election superintendent fails or refuses to
65 comply with this section, any elector of the City of Woodstock may apply for a writ of
66 mandamus to compel the municipal election superintendent to perform his or her duties
